gomodel:SYNGO_4668  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" , "Rationale: Figure 1E: Authors utilized a pHluorin reporter (super-ecliptic pHluorin: SEP) fused to the luminal C-terminal portions of Stx7 to image localization of Stx7 in cultured hippocampal neurons. Synaptic localization is shown for SEP-fused Stx7, co-stained with anti-Syb2 antibody. As a control for authentic SV residents, two widely used SEP constructs, SypHy (Synaptophysin (Syp) fused with SEP) (Fig. 1a) and VGLUT1-SEP were used.\n\nFigure 3A: Double immunostaining of Stx7 and Syp in cultured hippocampal neurons at 14 DIV shows synaptic localization of Stx7. The specificity of the Stx7 antibody was confirmed in independent experiments where Stx7 expression level was reduced by specific shRNA (Supplementary Fig. 14b).\n\nFigure 3C: Immunoelectron micrographs of SypHy and Stx7-SEP at presynaptic terminals shows localization of Stx7-SEP to a subpopulation of SVs at presynaptic terminals.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: - Primary hippocampal cultures were prepared from embryonic day 16 ICR mice\n- pHluorin reporter (super-ecliptic pHluorin: SEP) fused to the luminal C-terminal portions of Stx7\n- rabbit polyclonal anti-Stx7 antibody (BethylLaboratories; A304-512A),\n\n'\"To generate recombinant proteins as standards for quantification analysis, Stx7-NTD (a.a. 1-149) and Syb2-ΔTMD (a.a. 1-94) (accession no. NM_009497.3) were amplified by PCR, and cloned into the BamHI site and SalI site of pGEX6P-1. Lentiviral vectors carrying mCherry and either scrambled shRNA (CCTAAGGTTAAGTCGCCCTCG), mouse Stx7 shRNA-#1 (CGATATGATTGACAGCATAGA), or mouse Stx7 shRNA-#2; (GAAGCTGATATTATGGACATT) were obtained from VectorBuilder Biotechnology Co. Ltd.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4668" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

